{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17418278","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17418278"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T10:30:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T10:30:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261498"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261498"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14103"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17525938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17525938"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:18:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:18:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14103"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261498","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261498"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T10:29:54+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:32:06+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":2,"questionsAnswered":1,"marksTotal":1,"marksAttainable":1,"marksAttempted":1,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T10:30:03+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"14103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14103"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.06,0.02,0.05,0.73]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6773"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55938"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6773","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6773"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41487"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2770"},{"type":"tags","id":"2840"},{"type":"tags","id":"2843"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"14870"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43485"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55938"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a one-year history of progressive joint pain and stiffness in her hands, wrists, and feet. She reports morning stiffness lasting more than an hour. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her hands show bilateral swelling and tenderness of the metacarpophalangeal and proximal interphalangeal joints. There is ulnar deviation of the fingers and visible deformities of several digits.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn closer inspection of the right hand, the index finger shows hyperextension of the proximal interphalangeal joint and flexion of the distal interphalangeal joint. The middle finger demonstrates flexion of the proximal interphalangeal joint and hyperextension of the distal interphalangeal joint. The thumb shows hyperextension of the metacarpophalangeal joint and flexion of the interphalangeal joint.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the combination of hand deformities observed in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Swan neck, Bouchard\u0027s nodes, and Z-line deformity of the thumb","Swan neck, Boutonni\u00e8re, and Heberden\u0027s nodes","Boutonni\u00e8re, Bouchard\u0027s nodes, and Dupuytren\u0027s contracture","Boutonni\u00e8re, Swan neck, and Dupuytren\u0027s contracture","Swan neck, Boutonni\u00e8re, and Z-line deformity of the thumb"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic signs of rheumatoid arthritis (RA), including symmetrical joint involvement, morning stiffness, and characteristic hand deformities. The combination of deformities described in the stem is consistent with three common hand deformities seen in RA: swan neck deformity, boutonni\u00e8re deformity, and Z-line deformity of the thumb\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESwan neck, boutonni\u00e8re, and Z-line deformity of the thumb\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct combination of deformities observed in this patient. The index finger shows a swan neck deformity (hyperextension of the PIP joint and flexion of the DIP joint), the middle finger demonstrates a boutonni\u00e8re deformity (flexion of the PIP joint and hyperextension of the DIP joint), and the thumb exhibits a Z-thumb deformity (hyperextension of the MCP joint and flexion of the IP joint).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESwan neck, Bouchard\u0027s nodes, and Z-line deformity of the thumb\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because Bouchard\u0027s nodes are typically associated with osteoarthritis, not rheumatoid arthritis. Bouchard\u0027s nodes are bony enlargements of the PIP joints, which are not described in this patient\u0027s presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESwan neck, boutonni\u00e8re, and Heberden\u0027s nodes\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because Heberden\u0027s nodes, like Bouchard\u0027s nodes, are characteristic of osteoarthritis. They appear as bony enlargements of the DIP joints and are not mentioned in the stem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoutonni\u00e8re, Bouchard\u0027s nodes, and Dupuytren\u0027s contracture\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect for multiple reasons. Bouchard\u0027s nodes are not described, and Dupuytren\u0027s contracture is a separate condition affecting the palmar fascia, not typically associated with RA.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoutonni\u00e8re, swan neck, and Dupuytren\u0027s contracture\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because while it includes two of the correct deformities (boutonni\u00e8re and swan neck), it incorrectly includes Dupuytren\u0027s contracture instead of the Z-line deformity of the thumb described in the stem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these hand deformities is crucial for recognising and managing rheumatoid arthritis. Early diagnosis and treatment with disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs (DMARDs) can help minimise the progression and negative functional impact of these deformities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Swan neck deformity in rheumatoid arthritis is characterized by hyperextension of the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joint and flexion of the distal interphalangeal (DIP) joint.","Boutonni\u00e8re deformity in rheumatoid arthritis involves flexion of the PIP joint and hyperextension of the DIP joint.","Z-line deformity of the thumb in rheumatoid arthritis presents with hyperextension of the metacarpophalangeal (MCP) joint and flexion of the interphalangeal (IP) joint."],"references":["Mohammed RH, Goyal A, Bansal P. Hand and Wrist Rheumatoid Arthritis In: StatPearls [online]. 2023. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560890/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41487"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14103"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41487","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/41487"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-18T19:17:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-18T19:17:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6773"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55938"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"2770","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2770"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Rheumatoid arthritis","synonyms":["RA"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-08-02T12:37:02+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T08:37:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups